SECTION 8 — Ecosystem Services: Introduction & Classification
The Millennium Ecosystem Assessment (MEA, 2005) Framework
8.1 What are Ecosystem Services?
Ecosystem services are the benefits that humans obtain from ecosystems. The concept emphasises that
healthy ecosystems provide essential services — many of which have economic value — to human
society. The term was formalised by the Millennium Ecosystem Assessment (MEA, 2005), a
UN-commissioned global study involving 1,360 scientists from 95 countries.
Earlier framework: Costanza et al. (1997) published landmark paper in Nature estimating global
ecosystem services at $33 trillion/year (greater than global GNP at the time). This was a major
milestone in environmental economics.
